para.verbatim:
Return path to an MSVC executable program.
Tries to find the program in several places: first, one of the MSVC program search paths from the registry; next, the directories in the PATH environment variable. If any of those work, return an absolute path that is known to exist. If none of them work, just return the original program name, 'exe'.
Concrete class that implements an interface to Microsoft Visual C++, as defined by the CCompiler abstract class.
